1
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:03,866
(gentle music)

2
00:00:11,766 --> 00:00:14,333
(birds cawing)

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,733
- Hey.

4
00:00:28,766 --> 00:00:30,933
Race you to the monkey bars.

5
00:00:46,066 --> 00:00:47,666
You look like a Klingon that landed

6
00:00:47,700 --> 00:00:50,166
on your head on the Venice boardwalk.

7
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,433
- Stop showing off and come down from there.

8
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:56,333
(Vicki laughs)

9
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:04,100
(phone ringing)

10
00:01:04,133 --> 00:01:05,633
- You okay? - Yeah.

11
00:01:06,633 --> 00:01:09,300
(phone ringing)

12
00:01:10,666 --> 00:01:11,666
(dial tone ringing) - Hello.

13
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:18,633
- [Dispatcher] Parker Center to four-king-10,

14
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:20,333
patching through to four-king-20.

15
00:01:21,766 --> 00:01:23,300
- Four-king-10, over.

16
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,966
- Lieutenant, this is Harry McBride.

17
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,800
Sir, I'm sorry, I tried to reach you at home,

18
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,033
but no go there.

19
00:01:29,066 --> 00:01:30,433
I'm actually in your neighborhood now,

20
00:01:30,466 --> 00:01:31,766
across the street in the parking lot,

21
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:34,066
the Surf Side Fitness Center.

22
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:38,733
We have a stabbing victim, Caucasian woman, late 20s.

23
00:01:38,766 --> 00:01:40,833
Sir, I think you might want to come take a look at this one.

24
00:01:40,866 --> 00:01:43,000
- I'll be there in 10 minutes, Harry.

25
00:01:43,033 --> 00:01:44,100
Four-king-10 out.

26
00:01:46,033 --> 00:01:48,566
(dispatcher chattering on radio)

27
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:51,133
(solemn music)

28
00:02:11,166 --> 00:02:12,566
Harry.

29
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:13,700
- Lieutenant.

30
00:02:22,166 --> 00:02:24,700
- I gotta tell ya, I don't miss this.

31
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:25,666
- [Harry] No sir.

32
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:27,233
- Stan, what's up?

33
00:02:27,266 --> 00:02:29,766
- The victim's name is Rachel Kincaid, age 29.

34
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:32,200
She lives in Marina Del Rey, approximate time of death

35
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:34,833
six hours ago, she was leaving the gym.

36
00:02:34,866 --> 00:02:35,966
ME says it looks right-handed.

37
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,500
She was cut from the lower right,

38
00:02:37,533 --> 00:02:38,933
straight across the upper left.

39
00:02:38,966 --> 00:02:40,200
- We talk to family members yet?

40
00:02:40,233 --> 00:02:42,000
- We had her boyfriend here till about a half hour ago.

41
00:02:42,033 --> 00:02:43,433
We let him go.

42
00:02:43,466 --> 00:02:44,833
The rest of the family's back east.

43
00:02:44,866 --> 00:02:46,233
- Could he be a suspect?

44
00:02:46,266 --> 00:02:47,266
- No sir.

45
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,566
- He took one look and coughed up his breakfast.

46
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,733
We do have a witness.

47
00:02:49,766 --> 00:02:51,033
(siren trills)

48
00:02:51,066 --> 00:02:52,233
Blonde lady there, aerobics suit on,

49
00:02:52,266 --> 00:02:54,033
saw a white male, late 30s, leaving the lot in a hurry.

50
00:02:54,066 --> 00:02:55,633
- Okay, get her to a sketch artist,

51
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:57,900
have the full report on my desk by five o'clock.

52
00:02:57,933 --> 00:02:59,533
5:05 I'm outta there.

53
00:02:59,566 --> 00:03:01,133
- Sir, that's some rough life up there

54
00:03:01,166 --> 00:03:02,866
on the high command, eh?

55
00:03:02,900 --> 00:03:05,066
- It's one of the many perks of being a lieutenant.

56
00:03:06,033 --> 00:03:06,833
Carry on, Harry.

57
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:09,933
- Oh man.

58
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:18,233
- Whoa, whoa, don't sit down, this is the gift

59
00:03:18,266 --> 00:03:20,566
you had me pick up for Vicki, you have to do

60
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,566
the card yourself, that's where I draw the line.

61
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,600
- Great.

62
00:03:23,633 --> 00:03:24,533
What'd you think of it?

63
00:03:24,566 --> 00:03:25,966
- I'm impressed.

64
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:26,900
- Thanks, Lucille.

65
00:03:28,766 --> 00:03:30,233
- What did it cost?

66
00:03:30,266 --> 00:03:32,866
- Less than she would spend, more than you can afford.

67
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:34,233
- Ah.

68
00:03:34,266 --> 00:03:35,600
- Okay, you have a 9:15 robbery homicide meeting,

69
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,433
you have a briefing with the deputy chief,

70
00:03:37,466 --> 00:03:39,900
and mid-quarter reviews are due at the middle of this month,

71
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:42,000
which is tomorrow.

72
00:03:42,033 --> 00:03:44,166
- You're a regular calendar girl, Lucille Banks.

73
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,433
- I'll assume that's not a sexist remark

74
00:03:46,466 --> 00:03:49,033
for which I'll have to file harassment charges.

75
00:03:49,066 --> 00:03:51,500
Oh, oh, oh oh!

76
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:54,800
Your insurance check came in for the earthquake damage!

77
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:56,666
- Ah, great.

78
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,100
Been waiting months for this thing.

79
00:03:58,133 --> 00:04:00,466
I'm so tired of living out of a box, oh yeah.

80
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,900
- Well, if you need anything.

81
00:04:02,933 --> 00:04:04,533
- Lucille.

82
00:04:04,566 --> 00:04:05,400
Thank you.

83
00:04:07,166 --> 00:04:08,666
- Hi Captain. - Hey, Lucille.

84
00:04:09,633 --> 00:04:10,933
So, what you got there?

85
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,700
- Insurance check, Charlie.

86
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:14,633
- Hmm, about time. - Yeah.

87
00:04:14,666 --> 00:04:16,133
- So how you doing?

88
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:17,800
- Not bad for a Thursday.

89
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,300
What's on your mind?

90
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,266
- Oh, can't a guy come in and say "hello, how are ya?"

91
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,033
- Yeah, how are ya?

92
00:04:23,066 --> 00:04:24,200
- Great, how about you?

93
00:04:24,233 --> 00:04:25,666
- Well, it's Valentine's Day, Charlie,

94
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,633
and there was a murder this morning.

95
00:04:27,666 --> 00:04:28,466
- Yeah.

96
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,600
Hell of a city, huh?

97
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:31,200
- McBride is on it.

98
00:04:31,233 --> 00:04:32,733
- I want you to go easy on me.

99
00:04:34,433 --> 00:04:35,933
- You lost me.

100
00:04:35,966 --> 00:04:38,000
- Tomorrow night at my retirement roast.

101
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:39,133
Everybody's gonna be getting up

102
00:04:39,166 --> 00:04:39,900
telling their favorite little anecdote--

103
00:04:39,933 --> 00:04:41,100
- Just a second.

104
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,466
You think that I would stand up there

105
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:43,766
and tell some embarrassing story about you?

106
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,133
- That's exactly what I'm talking about,

107
00:04:45,166 --> 00:04:47,500
and if the Haskill incident is even metioned--

108
00:04:47,533 --> 00:04:48,466
- Yeah, Lucille.

109
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,100
- [Lucille] Vicki's on the line.

110
00:04:50,133 --> 00:04:51,833
- Well, hold that thought, Johnny.

111
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:53,966
Hi.

112
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,166
- Hi, honey.

113
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,933
I made great time, I just hope I can get back

114
00:04:56,966 --> 00:04:59,000
on the 405 before it becomes a parking lot.

115
00:04:59,033 --> 00:05:01,700
- I want you to know that I made reservations for two

116
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:04,233
tonight at eight o'clock at Picaccio's.

117
00:05:04,266 --> 00:05:05,266
- Picaccio's?

118
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:06,766
I'm impressed.

119
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:09,600
Dating habits have come a long way, Lieutenant Hunter.

120
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:11,233
- Well, we could go to Denny's,

121
00:05:11,266 --> 00:05:12,700
but after all, it is Valentine's Day.

122
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:16,533
- No, no, no, Picaccio's is just fine, hey Dad.

123
00:05:16,566 --> 00:05:17,733
- Hi dollface.

124
00:05:18,833 --> 00:05:20,200
- Let me talk to Rick.

125
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:21,700
- Tommy wants to say hello.

126
00:05:23,133 --> 00:05:24,433
- Did you buy Mom a present?

127
00:05:24,466 --> 00:05:25,966
It's Valentine's Day.

128
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,266
- Yup, sure did.

129
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:28,100
- What is it?

130
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,333
Tell me what it is.

131
00:05:29,366 --> 00:05:30,566
- Oh, I can't tell you what it is.

132
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,666
Your mom will show you when she gets home.

133
00:05:31,700 --> 00:05:33,066
- That's enough, Tommy.

134
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,700
Go on upstairs and get changed.

135
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:35,633
- [Tommy] Okay.

136
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:36,833
- Yeah, we saddle up right now,

137
00:05:36,866 --> 00:05:37,500
we can go riding before lunch, okay?

138
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:38,633
- All right!

139
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:39,900
- All right!

140
00:05:39,933 --> 00:05:41,533
- Listen, I have to swing by the office

141
00:05:41,566 --> 00:05:43,733
and then I need to referee the installation

142
00:05:43,766 --> 00:05:45,500
at the Brewstein house, he'll love the couches,

143
00:05:45,533 --> 00:05:48,066
he'll hate them when he finds out how much they cost.

144
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,666
Why don't I just meet you at the restaurant?

145
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:52,300
- That's a good idea.

146
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:54,900
- I love you, Lieutenant Hunter.

147
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:56,233
- I love you.

148
00:05:56,266 --> 00:05:57,400
- Bye.

149
00:05:57,433 --> 00:05:58,266
- Bye.

150
00:06:00,333 --> 00:06:02,000
- Real good to see you, baby.

151
00:06:02,033 --> 00:06:03,700
- I can't stay all day.

152
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:05,600
- Well, you're gonna stay for lunch,

153
00:06:05,633 --> 00:06:07,366
and then I'm gonna take Tommy fishing

154
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,000
and your sister's coming by with the baby,

155
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:10,633
and then you better right Avatar,

156
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:12,466
she's gonna die of neglect.

157
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:16,600
- I love it when you tell me what to do, Dad.

158
00:06:16,633 --> 00:06:17,866
I do.

159
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,100
- Lucille, where's that store again?

160
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:21,066
- Beverly Drive, south of Wilshire.

161
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,266
- I'll be in briefings and then

162
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:23,866
you can clock me out for lunch.

163
00:06:26,966 --> 00:06:27,766
- So.

164
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,600
- So what?

165
00:06:28,633 --> 00:06:29,833
- So tomorrow night.

166
00:06:29,866 --> 00:06:31,866
- Oh look, Charlie, tomorrow is your night,

167
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,766
your special night, there's no way I'd stand up there

168
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:35,633
and tell an embarrassing story about you.

169
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:36,833
No, no.

170
00:06:36,866 --> 00:06:38,700
Your friendship means way, way too much.

171
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:41,733
- Now, I know that's bull, I know what you're up to, Hunter!

172
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:46,633
(birds chirping)

173
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,500
- [Clerk] Thank you.

174
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:53,533
- [Frank] A little far west to see you, Lieutenant.

175
00:06:53,566 --> 00:06:55,233
- Well, believe it or not, Frank,

176
00:06:55,266 --> 00:06:56,900
I know how to find Beverly Hills.

177
00:06:58,700 --> 00:07:00,133
How long you been married?

178
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:02,400
- 23 glorious years.

179
00:07:02,433 --> 00:07:03,733
- What do you think of that?

180
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:11,900
- Well, I think the size of a ring isn't important,

181
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:15,366
it's the weight of the thought behind it that counts.

182
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:17,100
- You're a true politician, Frank.

183
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:18,833
- I'll take that as a compliment.

184
00:07:18,866 --> 00:07:20,100
- It was meant to be one.

185
00:07:21,466 --> 00:07:24,133
Oh, and by the way, Frank, listen, I wanna say

186
00:07:24,166 --> 00:07:26,633
thank you very much for the help on the Rodriguez case.

187
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:28,833
I never thought you'd push for murder one.

188
00:07:28,866 --> 00:07:30,500
- Neither did the Times.

189
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,000
That's why I did it.

190
00:07:32,033 --> 00:07:34,466
- Law and order look good on the campaign trail, Frank?

191
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,700
Especially now.

192
00:07:35,733 --> 00:07:38,333
- Oh no no, I'm only the district attorney.

193
00:07:38,366 --> 00:07:39,900
I am not officially a candidate

194
00:07:39,933 --> 00:07:41,800
for any other office in this state.

195
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,433
- How many times a day do you say that?

196
00:07:43,466 --> 00:07:46,966
- Oh, as many times as I can, Hunter. (chuckles)

197
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:47,933
Buh-bye, thank you.

198
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:55,200
- Yes. (chuckles)

199
00:07:55,233 --> 00:07:58,400
(gentle music)

200
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:00,300
Happy Valentine's Day.

201
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:02,633
- Neiman Marcus?

202
00:08:02,666 --> 00:08:03,900
Rick. - Open it.

203
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,766
- Oh, Rick.

204
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,433
It's gorgeous.

205
00:08:10,466 --> 00:08:12,066
- You remember we looked at that the other day?

206
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:13,533
- [Vicki] Yeah.

207
00:08:13,566 --> 00:08:15,166
- It's got a cute little place there for your (mumbles).

208
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,433
- Yeah, I know.

209
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,233
- Oh, your turn.

210
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:20,366
- For me?

211
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,366
- Happy Valentine's Day.

212
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,233
- Thanks.

213
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:25,533
Uh-oh.

214
00:08:25,566 --> 00:08:27,100
This looks like a serious gift.

215
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,800
"My Love Forever, Vicki."

216
00:08:45,566 --> 00:08:47,333
I must be the luckiest guy in the LAPD.

217
00:08:48,366 --> 00:08:49,533
- Oh, yeah.

218
00:08:49,566 --> 00:08:51,000
This coming from a man who owned a house

219
00:08:51,033 --> 00:08:53,366
on the Northridge fault line.

220
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,400
- Oh, listen.

221
00:08:54,433 --> 00:08:55,933
I finally got my insurance check.

222
00:08:55,966 --> 00:08:57,233
- Oh, great.

223
00:08:57,266 --> 00:08:58,533
You know, prices are still low,

224
00:08:58,566 --> 00:09:00,766
you should really think about buying something.

225
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,800
- Mm-hmm, I was thinking maybe the Hollywood Hills.

226
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,700
- Too many mud slides.

227
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:04,600
- Topanga Canyon.

228
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:07,766
- Charlie lost his place there in the fire.

229
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,000
- You're right about that.

230
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:15,033
- You should move into my place in Malibu, bank the money.

231
00:09:17,966 --> 00:09:19,600
- No, I don't think I could take advantage

232
00:09:19,633 --> 00:09:24,633
of a successful professional woman such as yourself.

233
00:09:25,366 --> 00:09:26,300
But we could fix that.

234
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:34,000
You could marry me.

235
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:39,433
- Oh, Rick.

236
00:09:40,666 --> 00:09:42,733
- What do you say, Vicki?

237
00:09:44,566 --> 00:09:45,566
- I say yes.

238
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:39,433
(sinister music)

239
00:10:39,466 --> 00:10:40,266
Rick.

240
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:05,066
(car engine starting)

241
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:08,100
(suspenseful music)

242
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,333
- Black Mercedes.

243
00:11:26,366 --> 00:11:28,333
(Vicki sighs)

244
00:11:28,366 --> 00:11:29,866
- Why won't he leave me alone?

245
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,333
It's been two years, for god's sake.

246
00:11:33,366 --> 00:11:35,366
- I'll take care of this in the morning.

247
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:50,600
(elevator bell dings) (people chattering)

248
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:53,933
- Elizabeth, that looks terrific.

249
00:11:53,966 --> 00:11:55,500
- [Elizabeth] Thank you, Harry.

250
00:11:56,433 --> 00:11:57,200
- Sam, hi. - Harry.

251
00:11:57,233 --> 00:11:58,733
- Hey Lar.

252
00:11:58,766 --> 00:12:00,466
- [Man] If you can get a handle on that,

253
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:01,233
I'd really appreciate it, because I've

254
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:02,500
got a meeting with--

255
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:03,600
- Lieutenant.

256
00:12:03,633 --> 00:12:05,100
Sir.

257
00:12:05,133 --> 00:12:06,800
I'm afraid we're out of luck on the Kincaid case.

258
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:09,466
The line at the coroner's office was around the block.

259
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:12,133
I did, however, manage to dip into the favor bank

260
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:14,733
and procure this.

261
00:12:14,766 --> 00:12:16,466
- Oh, Harry, you are a sweetheart.

262
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:26,600
I knew they had their problems.

263
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:29,400
I didn't think it went this far.

264
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:30,500
- I'm afraid so, sir.

265
00:12:31,866 --> 00:12:34,300
Evidently two NBA championships will buy you a sealed file

266
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:36,766
plus a couple hundred hours of community service.

267
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:42,600
