01:20:48,200 --> 01:20:49,966
- Been expecting you, Jack.

1569
01:20:52,333 --> 01:20:53,966
- You made a fool outta me.

1570
01:20:54,000 --> 01:20:56,133
- I made a fool outta you?

1571
01:20:56,166 --> 01:20:58,100
Did what you asked, put you on television.

1572
01:21:02,600 --> 01:21:03,633
- Are we alone?

1573
01:21:04,733 --> 01:21:05,866
- It's just me and you.

1574
01:21:08,466 --> 01:21:10,566
- Well, why don't you come out and play, Hunter?

1575
01:21:10,600 --> 01:21:13,000
(gun clicks)

1576
01:21:15,200 --> 01:21:16,700
- Sealed off every exit, Jack.

1577
01:21:18,066 --> 01:21:20,266
No way out, just me and you.

1578
01:21:27,166 --> 01:21:29,366
(gunshot bangs)

1579
01:21:29,400 --> 01:21:32,400
(suspenseful music)

1580
01:21:35,166 --> 01:21:37,800
Jack, I'm gonna say this one time.

1581
01:21:37,833 --> 01:21:41,533
Drop your weapon and lay face down on the floor,

1582
01:21:41,566 --> 01:21:43,133
put your hands behind your back.

1583
01:21:44,533 --> 01:21:47,200
(gunshot bangs)

1584
01:21:48,233 --> 01:21:49,633
I'm gonna take that as a no.

1585
01:21:54,600 --> 01:21:57,533
(gunshots banging)

1586
01:22:03,400 --> 01:22:06,433
(electricity buzzes)

1587
01:22:16,233 --> 01:22:18,733
(Rick grunts)

1588
01:22:32,866 --> 01:22:34,566
(Rick groans)

1589
01:22:34,600 --> 01:22:36,100
- Very persistent, Hunter.

1590
01:22:42,366 --> 01:22:43,266
Hang on, Hunter.

1591
01:22:43,300 --> 01:22:45,500
They got a home game on Tuesday.

1592
01:23:17,166 --> 01:23:18,000
- Valko.

1593
01:23:20,533 --> 01:23:21,833
I have confession to make.

1594
01:23:22,900 --> 01:23:24,166
I lied.

1595
01:23:24,200 --> 01:23:25,400
We're not alone.

1596
01:23:26,300 --> 01:23:28,533
See 'em down near the lights?

1597
01:23:28,566 --> 01:23:30,833
The media, they're all for you.

1598
01:23:35,500 --> 01:23:36,433
- Getting anything?

1599
01:23:42,333 --> 01:23:45,633
- This is your 15 seconds of fame, Jack.

1600
01:23:45,666 --> 01:23:48,966
- It's 15 minutes, you idiot.

1601
01:23:49,000 --> 01:23:50,400
- No.

1602
01:23:50,433 --> 01:23:52,233
I think I got it right in your case.

1603
01:23:54,766 --> 01:23:57,033
You're gonna spend the rest of your life in jail, Jack.

1604
01:24:00,133 --> 01:24:03,000
(cameras clicking)

1605
01:24:06,266 --> 01:24:09,633
You know how hard it is for me not to kill you?

1606
01:24:09,666 --> 01:24:12,333
(Jack laughing)

1607
01:24:16,600 --> 01:24:17,433
- I gotta go.

1608
01:24:18,800 --> 01:24:21,333
(Jack shouting)

1609
01:24:21,366 --> 01:24:24,166
(cameras clicking)

1610
01:24:24,200 --> 01:24:26,700
(Jack shouting)

1611
01:24:26,733 --> 01:24:31,733
(glass shattering) (people gasping)

1612
01:24:32,900 --> 01:24:35,366
(cameras clicking) (people chattering)

1613
01:24:35,400 --> 01:24:37,333
- I got the whole shot.

1614
01:24:43,766 --> 01:24:46,466
(cameras clicking)

1615
01:24:46,500 --> 01:24:49,033
- We knew from the start that Matt Sherry was innocent,

1616
01:24:49,066 --> 01:24:50,500
and that's why we delayed in asking

1617
01:24:50,533 --> 01:24:51,900
the grand jury for an indictment.

1618
01:24:51,933 --> 01:24:54,766
Now what we had here was a media frenzy,

1619
01:24:54,800 --> 01:24:57,566
without the benefit of the facts that we had in hand.

1620
01:24:57,600 --> 01:24:59,200
Now, any questions, anybody?

1621
01:24:59,233 --> 01:25:00,266
- [Reporter] Sir, are you running for

1622
01:25:00,300 --> 01:25:01,266
United States Senator?

1623
01:25:01,300 --> 01:25:03,300
- Remind me to keep up with this guy, will you?

1624
01:25:04,900 --> 01:25:07,400
- Yeah, right. (chuckles)

1625
01:25:07,433 --> 01:25:10,333
- No no no, I'm just glad this whole ordeal has ended

1626
01:25:10,366 --> 01:25:12,566
and I can turn my attention back to my son.

1627
01:25:13,400 --> 01:25:15,100
And my team.

1628
01:25:15,133 --> 01:25:17,133
I'm very grateful to Lieutenant Rick Hunter

1629
01:25:17,166 --> 01:25:19,800
for encouraging me to seek counseling

1630
01:25:19,833 --> 01:25:23,533
regarding my inexcusable behavior towards women.

1631
01:25:23,566 --> 01:25:26,133
(solemn music)

1632
01:25:35,500 --> 01:25:37,500
- Hey, how was the fishing, buddy?

1633
01:25:37,533 --> 01:25:38,433
- [Tommy] It was great.

1634
01:25:38,466 --> 01:25:40,966
- Ah, that's good, that's good.

1635
01:25:41,800 --> 01:25:42,800
- Matt.

1636
01:25:42,833 --> 01:25:43,666
- Thanks.

1637
01:26:48,133 --> 01:26:50,566
- [Vicki] My darling Lieutenant Hunter.

1638
01:26:50,600 --> 01:26:52,033
I know it's awfully formal of me

1639
01:26:52,066 --> 01:26:53,233
to write you a thank you note,

1640
01:26:53,266 --> 01:26:55,133
but it's something I was always nagged to do

1641
01:26:55,166 --> 01:26:58,133
by my mother, may she rest in peace.

1642
01:26:58,166 --> 01:27:01,000
The ring is so beautiful, but not nearly

1643
01:27:01,033 --> 01:27:02,433
as beautiful as you.

1644
01:27:02,466 --> 01:27:05,400
It symbolizes the happiness you've brought to me,

1645
01:27:05,433 --> 01:27:07,100
and will always be a constant reminder

1646
01:27:07,133 --> 01:27:09,400
of the place you hold in my heart.

1647
01:27:09,433 --> 01:27:13,266
Together we will have the family we've always talked about.

1648
01:27:13,300 --> 01:27:16,200
Again I say yes to your proposal.

1649
01:27:17,200 --> 01:27:18,800
My love forever, Vicki.

1650
01:27:20,500 --> 01:27:23,100
(solemn music)

1651
01:27:44,433 --> 01:27:47,000
(solemn music)

